    "Despite the rapid development has got for GCNs, most of the GCNs are shallow structures.",
    "At present, some researchers have begun to train deep GCNs using different methods.",
    "GraphSAGE simultaneously uses node feature and structural feature to obtain graph embeddings, which is more scalable.",
    "In 2017, Pham proposed CLN (Pham et al., 2017) for relational classification, where model performance peaks when the depth of CLN reaches 10 layers, and model performance decreases as the increasing depth of CLN.",
    "In 2018, Rahimi et al. (2018) used GCN to integrate user text with network structures to achieve a more accurate geolocation of social media users."
